The paper deals with the problem of registration of pre-operative 3-D volumes to intra-operative 2-D X-ray images, which is a common problem in medical image analysis. The proposed method involves the use of PointNet for estimating optimal weights for correspondences, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of robotics and medical imaging, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of machine learning techniques for correspondence weighting suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
